  <section>
  <h2>What are {{name}}'s Political Positions?</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <b>Housing:</b> Economou opposes several initiatives to make housing affordable, including rent stabilization and a small fee on high-end real estate transactions to create an affordable housing fund. When asked what policies support to keep Worcester affordable, he gave no answer. <sup><a href="{{surveyLink}}" target="_blank">source</a></sup>
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Education</b>: Economou wants to build a new Burncoat High School and opposes the expansion of charter schools. <sup><a href="{{surveyLink}}" target="_blank">source</a></sup>
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Public Trandsportation:</b> Economou opposes fare-free buses, a wildly-popular transportation program that <a href="https://www.telegram.com/story/business/transportation/2024/04/18/wrta-vote-free-bus-rides-in-worcester-to-continue-into-2025/73358982007/" target="_blank">provides 3-4 million free trips annually</a>, and is supported by <a href="https://spectrumnews1.com/ma/worcester/news/2025/06/25/free-bus-fare-wrta-regional-transit" target="_blank">70% of Worcester residents</a>. He also opposes the expansion of protected bike lanes in the city, including the Mill Street redesign that has <a href="https://theworcesterguardian.org/f/council-presses-for-answers-on-mill-street-safety-costs-steps">reduced automotive speeding and crashes</a>. <sup><a href="{{surveyLink}}" target="_blank">source</a></sup>
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Immigration</b>: When asked "What can your city do to help protect immigrant communities under ICE and ensure genuine community safe?", Economou simply answered, "The community is safe". <sup><a href="{{surveyLink}}" target="_blank">3</a></sup>
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Sustainability</b>: Economou opposes adopting building codes that would mandate new construction and renovations make use of modern, high-efficiency heating and cooling systems. <sup><a href="{{surveyLink}}" target="_blank">source</a></sup>
    </li>
  </ul>

